(fifthQuint)Comparison of GSKBiologicals' Hib-MenCY-TT Vaccine vs Licensed Hib Conjugate or Meningococcal Vaccine.

 The non-inferiority of the immunogenicity, safety, and antibody persistence of Hib-MenCY-TT vaccine will be compared to ActHIB(R), a monovalent Hib conjugate vaccine licensed in the US.

 All subjects will be vaccinated at 2, 4, 6, and 12 to 15 months.

 The immunogenicity of the MenC and MenY antigens will be summarized.

 MenC and MenY immunogenicity will be compared to Menomune(R) (a quadrivalent meningococcal A, C, Y, and W-135 plain polysaccharide vaccine licensed in the US) administered to children 3 to 5 years of age.

